Consider the following synchronization code:
int turn = 0;
// Process 0
while (true) {
 flag[0] = true;
 while (flag[1]) {
 if (turn == 1) {
 flag[0] = false;
 while (turn == 1);
 flag[0] = true;
 }
 }
 critical_section();
 turn = 1;
 flag[0] = false;
 remainder_section();
}
(a) Identify this algorithm. (b) Explain how it solves the critical section problem. (c) What are its limitations?
